=Contact Details=

==RexxLA==

The Rexx Language Association manages the ooRexx project.
[http://www.rexxla.org/contact.html Contact details for RexxLA].

==Development Team==

The ooRexx Development Team is:

* '''David Ashley''' &lt;wdashley@users.sourceforge.net&gt; '''Project Administrator'''<br />
David has over 15 years experience with the Rexx language and writing external function packages for Rexx.
He is the author of the OS/2 GammaTech Rexx Superset/2 product and many shareware and freeware packages.
In addition, David  has extensive experience in the open source community and is the project leader for three
SourceForge projects:
[http://sourceforge.net/projects/modrexx/ Mod_Rexx],
[http://sourceforge.net/projects/gtkrxdlg/ GTKRxDlg], and
[http://sourceforge.net/projects/os2linux/ OS2Linux].
He has worked on projects using everything from embedded processors up to large IBM mainframes.
He has over 20 years of software development experience using multiple architectures, development environments,
tools, and operating systems.
* '''Rony Flatscher''' &lt;orexx@users.sourceforge.net&gt; '''Test Team Lead'''<br />
Rony is the author of several small Rexx utilities (e.g.
[http://hobbes.nmsu.edu/pub/os2/dev/rexx/datergf2.zip datergf2.zip])
and the external Rexx function package
[http://wi.wu-wien.ac.at/rgf/rexx/bsf4rexx/ BSF4Rexx]
(allows Rexx to be used from Java, and allows Rexx to use all of the Java functionality, cf.
[http://www.rexxla.org/Symposium/2003/Sym2003Presentations.html The 2003 International Rexx Symposium] or
[http://www.rexxla.org/Symposium/2004/schedule.html The 2004 International Rexx Symposium]).
<br />
He works as a professor for Business informatics (&quot;Wirtschaftsinformatik&quot;) at the
[http://www.wu-wien.ac.at/english Vienna University of Economics and Business Administration]
[http://www.wu-wien.ac.at (Wirtschaftsuniversit&auml;t Wien)]
and uses Open Object Rexx for teaching Business Administration and MIS students the object-oriented
paradigm, as well as remote-controlling (automating) Windows and Windows end-user applications
(e.g. MS Office, Open Office) as well as Java and Java applications.
* '''Mark Hessling''' &lt;rexx@users.sourceforge.net&gt; '''Project Manager'''<br />
Mark is the author of several Rexx external function packages, such as
[http://rexxsql-rexx.sf.net Rexx/SQL],
[http://rexxdw.sf.net Rexx/DW],
[http://rexxgd.sf.net Rexx/gd],
[http://rexxcurl.sf.net Rexx/CURL],
[http://rexxcurses.sf.net Rexx/Curses],
[http://rexxtrans.sf.net Rexx/Trans],
[http://rexxwrapper.sf.net Rexx/Wrapper].
Mark is also the current principal maintainer of
[http://regina-rexx.sf.net The Regina Rexx Interpreter],
[http://rexxtk.sf.net Rexx/tk], and
[http://pdcurses.sf.net PDCurses].
In his spare time, Mark is the Webmaster for RexxLA, and is a Volunteer Rural Fire
Fighter.
* '''Rick McGuire''' &lt;bigrixx@users.sourceforge.net&gt; '''Principal Architect'''<br />
Rick was the developer charged with integrating Mike Cowlishaw's
original Rexx interpreter into VM/CMS back in 1982.  From 1982 until
1995, Rick was IBM's lead architect for Rexx issues and principal
developer of the Classic Rexx and Object Rexx interpreters for OS/2.
Since 1995, Rick has been heavily involved in IBM projects involving
programming languages, including 3 years as a member of IBM's Java
Virtual Machine development team.

